general.noPossibleVisualizations: Visualisation cannot be formed with the selected values. Try changing your selection.
general.editorTitle: Selecting variables and making a visualisation

tableSelect.title: Select the database table from the directory tree that is the source for the visualisation data.

variableSelect.selectable: Move the mark to the right to allow the variable to be browsed
variableSelect.title: Select the values manually from the variables or utilise the dynamic alternatives in the menu. The user interface is updated immediately according to your selections.

editor.contentLanguage: Edit language versions of the visualisation

saveDialog.saveOptions: Select in which format you want to save

saveResultDialog.errorMessage: Check the variable selections and try again.
saveResultDialog.pleaseWait: Please wait, this may take a moment for published queries.

error.contentVariableMissing: Content variable missing from the table. Please contact the producer of this table or maintenance.
error.timeVariableMissing: Time variable missing from the table. Please contact the producer of this table or maintenance.
error.variablesMissingValues: Variable values missing from the table. Please contact the producer of this table or maintenance.

cellCount.infoText: The number of cells in the selection
cellCount.warningText: The number of cells in your selection is close to the maximum.
cellCount.dangerText: The number of selected cells exceeds the maximum. Select fewer values for visualisation to succeed.

previewGuide.tooSmallQuery: Visualisation can be viewed only when a value is selected for each variable.
previewGuide.impossibleToVisualize: You can view the possible visualisation types when you have selected at least one value for each variable.

infoText.treeSelection: Select the PX table from the directory tree that is the source for the visualisation data.
infoText.langSelector: Select the language to be shown in the user interface menus
infoText.langTab: Edit the necessary data in different language versions. Correct the headings at least.
infoText.selectableButton: If you want the visualisation for this variable to be selectable, select "Selectable". In this case, the user can change the variable value in the visualisation.
infoText.selectableInput: You can select the default value of the variable visible in the visualisation, which the user sees before making their own selections.
infoText.titleEdition: Edit the heading of the visualisation to be as clear as possible. Keep FIRST/LAST at least in updated visualisations, so the time variables in the heading are updated automatically.
infoText.metaEdition: Edit the writing of the visualisation metadata if necessary.
infoText.visualizationSelection: Select the visualisation type you want. If the graph type you want is not possible, see the button "Other chart types" for further information.
infoText.otherVisualizations: The "Other chart types" button can be used to view the reasons for the rejection of missing graph types. PxGraf enables graph types in accordance with the recommendations of statistical graphics.
infoText.visualizationConfiguration: Edit visualisation. Different visualisations have different editing options.
infoText.save: Save the finished graph/table and store the identifier. Select a frozen static option for the release and a dynamic updated option for the statistics page in the dialogue which opens by clicking "Save".
infoText.rescaleButtons: Visualisation adapts automatically to displays of different sizes. Test what the visualisation looks like in different sizes.

selectable.labelText: Default value of the variable visible in the visualisation

savedQuery.errorMsg: Check the visualisation identifier and try again.

titleWarning.maxLengthText: The maximum length of the heading is

visualizationSettings.showDataPoints: Show data values in the graph
